player_note.headline: Nabs power-play assist
player_note.text:
Hughes logged a power-play assist and four shots on goal in Wednesday's 5-1 win over the Bruins.

Advice: Hughes had been held off the scoresheet over the prior two games, which had seen the Devils limited to a total of two goals against the Flyers and Senators. The 23-year-old was able to get back on the scoresheet Wednesday when he assisted on a Stefan Noesen tally in the second period. Hughes is up to 56 points (25 on the power play), 185 shots on net and a plus-9 rating over 50 appearances this season.

player_note.headline: Three-point night for top-10 scorer
player_note.text:
Hughes scored and had two assists in a 4-3 overtime loss to Toronto on Thursday.

Advice: Hughes is right there with the offensive heavyweights in the NHL, and he's currently eighth overall with 55 points (18 goals, 37 assists), plus 179 shots in 47 games. Hughes is on pace to top 310 shots, which elevates his value even more in leagues that count that category. Volume shooters can sometimes make or break your fantasy week in leagues count that category.

player_outlooks.headline: Fantasy Hockey 2024 Player Outlook
player_outlooks.text: During the 2023-24 season, Hughes scored 27 goals and 74 points in 62 games. He got off to a strong start with five goals and 15 assists in nine contests, but then a shoulder injury forced him out of the lineup. Although Hughes did return, he would later miss the final four games of the season due to shoulder surgery. The silver lining is he's expected to make a full recovery in time for training camp. Despite missing some action, Hughes remained productive throughout the year, recording a career-high average of 4.42 shots per game and leading the Devils with 31 power-play points. In the 2022-23 campaign, Hughes was just one point shy of reaching 100 points, a mark he should surpass this season if he can avoid injuries.
